  QL_Kakariko_Ch_006_Desc:
    contents:
      - text: "When Rola, owner of the general store, judged\nme as a capable archer, she wasted no time\nrecruiting me for a seemingly simple job.\n\nAll she asked was that I \""
      - control:
          kind: set_colour
          colour: red
      - text: "light the torches\nby the Goddess Statue"
      - control:
          kind: reset_colour
      - text: "\" in the village, but her\nsuspiciously sweet smile made it clear that\nthis task would require unconventional methods."
  QL_Kakariko_Ch_006_Finish:
    contents:
      - text: "In lighting the torches, I seem to have also\nignited Rola's passion. The day that she\ncan reunite with her husband may not be so\nfar off."
  QL_Kakariko_Ch_006_Light:
    contents:
      - text: "\""
      - control:
          kind: set_colour
          colour: red
      - text: Light the torches by the Goddess Statue
      - control:
          kind: reset_colour
      - text: ".\"\n\nI did as Rola asked and lit the torches.\nI'll go to the general store and tell her\nthat what she requested is done."
  QL_Kakariko_Ch_006_Name:
    contents:
      - text: Arrows of Burning Heat
